GM staff |url=http://www.egmmag.com/article2/0,4364,1489711,00.asp |title=Dead or Alive Xtreme Volleyball |magazine=[[Electronic Gaming Monthly]] |issue=164 |date=March 2003 |page=130 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040227231415/http://www.egmmag.com/article2/0%2C4364%2C1489711%2C00.asp |archivedate=2004-02-27 |url-status=dead |accessdate=2014-10-25 }}</ref>\n| EuroG = 3/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Bramwell |first=Tom |date=2003-03-25 |url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/r_doax_x |title=Dead or Alive Xtreme Beach Volleyball |website=[[Eurogamer]] |accessdate=2014-10-25}}</ref>\n| GI = 7.5/10<ref>{{cite journal |last=Helgeson |first=Matt |url=http://gameinformer.com/Games/Review/200303/R03.0729.1709.30269.htm |archive-url=https://archive.is/20070528113350/http://gameinformer.com/Games/Review/200303/R03.0729.1709.30269.htm |url-status=dead |archive-date=2007-05-28 |title=Dead or Alive Xtreme Beach Volleyball |magazine=[[Game Informer]] |issue=119 |date=March 2003 |page=87 |accessdate=2014-10-25}}</ref>\n| GamePro = {{Rating|5|5}}<ref>{{cite magazine |author=Tokyo Drifter |date=2003-01-22 |url=http://gamepro.com/microsoft/xbox/games/reviews/27873.shtml |title=Dead or Alive Xtreme Beach Volleyball Review for Xbox on GamePro.com |magazine=[[GamePro]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050206185354/http://gamepro.com/microsoft/xbox/games/reviews/27873.shtml |archivedate=2005-02-06 |url-status=dead |accessdate=2014-10-25}}</ref>\n| GameRev = B\u2212<ref>{{cite web |last=Liu |first=Johnny |date=February 2003 |url=http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/doa-xtreme-beach-volleyball |title=DOA Xtreme Beach Volleyball Review |publisher=[[Game Revolution]] |accessdate=2014-10-25}}</ref>\n| GSpot = 6/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Gerstmann |first=Jeff |date=2003-01-22 |url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/dead-or-alive-xtreme-beach-volleyball-review/1900-2909414/ |title=Dead or Alive Xtreme Beach Volleyball Review |website=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=2014-10-25}}</ref>\n| GSpy = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last=Padilla |first=Raymond |date=2003-01-26 |url=http://xbox.gamespy.com/xbox/dead-or-alive-xtreme-beach-volleyball/5556p1.html |title=GameSpy: Dead or Alive Xtreme Beach Volleyball |publisher=[[GameSpy]] |accessdate=2014-10-25}}</ref>\n| GameZone = 9.2/10<ref name=GameZone/>\n| IGN = 9.2/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Boulding |first=Aaron |date=2003-01-22 |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2003/01/22/dead-or-alive-xtreme-beach-volleyball-review |title=Dead or Alive Xtreme Beach Volleyball Review |website=[[IGN]] |accessdate=2014-10-25}}</ref>\n| OXM = 8.4/10<ref>{{cite journal |title=Dead or Alive Xtreme Beach Volleyball |magazine=[[Official Xbox Magazine]] |date=March 2003 |page=72}}</ref>\n| rev1 = ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''\n| rev1Score = B<ref name=EW>{{cite journal |last=Walk |first=Gary Eng |url=http://www.ew.com/article/2003/02/07/dead-or-alive-xtreme-beach-volleyball |title=DEAD OR ALIVE XTREME BEACH VOLLEYBALL Review |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |issue=694 |date=2003-02-07 |page=90 |accessdate=2014-10-25}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Playboy]]''\n| rev2Score = 74%<ref name=Playboy>{{cite journal |url=http://www.playboy.com/arts-entertainment/games/xtremebeachvolleyball/index.html |title=Dead or Alive: Xtreme Beach Volleyball |magazine=[[Playboy]] |year=2003 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040222014704/http://www.playboy.com/arts-entertainment/games/xtremebeachvolleyball/index.html |archivedate=2004-02-22 |url-status=dead |accessdate=2014-10-29}}</ref>\n}}\n\nReviewers were mostly positive, especially to the depth of the volleyball game, as well as with the high quality of the visuals and animation.<ref name=GameZone>{{cite web | url=http://xbox.gamezone.com/gzreviews/r20536.htm | title=Dead or Alive Xtreme Beach Volleyball Review | last=Valentino | first=Nick | publisher=GameZone | date=2003-02-03 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081006122131/http://xbox.gamezone.com/gzreviews/r20536.htm | archivedate=2008-10-06 | url-status=dead | accessdate=2014-10-25}}</ref> Review scores ranged from poor to very high, resulting in the averaged ratings of 74% at [[GameRankings]]<ref name=\"GR\" /> and 73/100 at [[Metacritic]].<ref name=\"MC\" />\n\nIn its review, ''[[Edge (magazine)|Edge]]'' focused on the game's unusual social, rather than adversarial, focus.<ref name=Edge>{{cite journal|author=Edge staff |title=Dead or Alive Xtreme Beach Volleyball |magazine=[[Edge (magazine)|Edge]] |issue=121 |date=March 2003 |page=86}}</ref> ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]'' gave the game a score of eight out of ten and stated that \"The sharp graphics and advanced [[Breast physics|jiggle physics]] will no doubt prick the interest of lonely gamers, but surprisingly, the game's volleyball action is pretty solid. And that's the most important thing... right?\"<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Porter |first=Alex |date=2003-01-22 |url=http://www.maximonline.com/entertainment/reviews/review_games_4654.html |title=Dead or Alive Xtreme Beach Volleyball |magazine=[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20030122141518/http://www.maximonline.com/entertainment/reviews/review_games_4654.html |archivedate=2003-01-22 |url-status=dead |accessdate=2014-10-25}}</ref> ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' gave it a B and said, \"It's kinda difficult not to get caught up in this goofy title, as you use your v-ball winnings to buy shoes and skimpy clothes for your fellow beach bunnies.\"<ref name=EW/> ''[[Playboy]]'' gave it a score of 74% and said, \"As long as you know what you're in for, ''DOA: Xtreme Beach Volleyball'' can be a mildly entertaining collection of digital diversions with, at the very least, the best-looking virtual women to grace a video game.\"<ref name=Playboy/>\n\nAt the first [[VGX (award show)|Spike Video Game Awards]] in 2003, ''Dead or Alive Xtreme Beach Volleyball '' won in the category Best Animation.<ref>\"Spike TV honors digital women, Ray Liotta in video game awards\", ''The Victoria Advocate'', December 4, 2003.</ref> In 2006, [[GamesRadar]] ranked [[gravure idol|gravure]] scenes in the game to be one of the 100 greatest gaming moment in history.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamesradar.com/101-greatest-gaming-moments-day-one/?page=10 |title=101 Greatest Gaming Moments, Day One (Page 10) |publisher=[[GamesRadar]] |date=2006-11-07 |accessdate=2014-10-25}}</ref>\n\n===Controversy===\nShortly after the game's launch, a community of hobbyist hackers reverse engineered ''Dead or Alive Extreme Volleyball''\u2019s texture system, allowing users to modify textures of the player character models. This quickly led to users replacing the already revealing swimsuits with high detailed nude textures include genitalia and pubic hair for all in game characters. This resulted in fully nude female characters that would lounge about and play volleyball with full breast and buttocks physics intact. In January 2005, ninjahacker.net was taken to court by Tecmo for breaching the [[Digital Millennium Copyright Act]] by [[reverse engineering]] aspects of the game, as well as ''[[Ninja Gaiden (2004 video game)|Ninja Gaiden]]'' and ''[[Dead or Alive 2]]''. The company was seeking between $1,000 and $10,000 for every skin swapped over the community website.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/pictures/the-most-offensive-video-games-to-women/4/ |title=The most offensive video games to women |publisher=CBS News |date=2017-08-17 |accessdate=2017-08-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2005/02/10/tecmo_sues_xbox_game_hackers/ |title=Tecmo Sues Xbox Game Hackers |website=[[The Register]] |date=2005-03-10 |accessdate=2012-11-12}}</ref>\n\n{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100227100434/http://www.tecmo.co.jp/teamninja/product_bv.htm Official website]\n*{{MobyGames|id=/xbox/dead-or-alive-xtreme-beach-volleyball}}\n\n{{Dead or Alive series}}\n{{Team Ninja|state=collapsed}}\n{{Tomo